# Top Concepts to Know for the AZ-900 Exam

The AZ-900 exam is an entry-level certification offered by Microsoft that tests your knowledge of cloud computing basics and the Azure platform. Whether you're a cloud beginner or an experienced IT professional looking to expand your skillset, passing the AZ-900 exam can be a valuable addition to your resume. Here are the top concepts to know for the AZ-900 exam:

## Cloud Computing Fundamentals

First and foremost, the AZ-900 exam covers the basics of cloud computing, including key characteristics of cloud services, cloud deployment models, and cloud service models. Be sure to understand the differences between public, private, and hybrid cloud deployment models, as well as Infrastructure-as-a-Service (IaaS), Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS), and Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) cloud service models.

## Azure Services

The AZ-900 exam also covers various Azure services, including compute, storage, networking, and database services. You should be familiar with the different types of virtual machines available in Azure, as well as Azure's storage offerings, such as Blob storage and Azure Files. Additionally, you should understand Azure's networking capabilities, such as Virtual Network (VNet) and Azure Load Balancer.

## Security, Privacy, Compliance, and Trust

One of the key concerns with cloud computing is security, and the AZ-900 exam tests your knowledge of Azure's security, privacy, compliance, and trust capabilities. You should be familiar with Azure's security features, such as Azure Active Directory, and Azure's compliance certifications, such as SOC and ISO. Additionally, you should understand Azure's privacy commitments and data protection capabilities.

## Pricing and Support

Finally, the AZ-900 exam covers Azure pricing and support options. You should understand Azure's pricing model, including pay-as-you-go and reserved instances, as well as Azure's free and trial offerings. Additionally, you should be familiar with Azure's support options, such as Azure Support Plans and Azure Advisor.

## Conclusion

The AZ-900 exam is a valuable certification for IT professionals looking to demonstrate their cloud computing knowledge and skills. By understanding the key concepts of cloud computing fundamentals, Azure services, security, privacy, compliance, trust, pricing, and support, you can increase your chances of passing the exam and advancing your career in cloud computing. Good luck!
